tasks.description:
Create src/chat/multi-agent.ts. Export async function runMultiAgent(prompt, personaIds: string[], personaManager, contextBuilder, llmService, tree, nodeId): for each personaId, build context with that persona's system prompt. Use Promise.allSettled to run all LLM calls in parallel. Collect results: {personaId, label, response}[]. Then build an orchestration prompt: 'Here are perspectives from multiple mathematical experts:

[Algebraist]: {response1}

[Analyst]: {response2}
...

Synthesize these perspectives into a comprehensive answer.' Send to LLM, collect synthesis. Return {individualResponses, synthesis}. Read configurable persona list from mathAgent.multiAgent.personas setting (default: ['algebraist','analyst','geometer']). Add setting to package.json.

Create src/webview/handlers/lean4-handler.ts. Register 'verifyLean4' handler: get node content from tree, send to LLM with prompt 'Translate this mathematical statement/proof into Lean4 code. Return only the Lean4 code block.', get lean4 code from response, call panel.services.lean4Service.verify(code), store result in node.metadata.lean4Result, save tree, post {type:'lean4Result', nodeId, result}. Register 'retryLean4' handler {nodeId, attempt}: get previous result, send to LLM with 'The following Lean4 code failed:
{code}
Errors:
{diagnostics}
Fix the code.' Re-verify. Max 3 attempts (check attempt < 3). Import and call registerLean4Handlers in panel.ts constructor. In ResearchTab: render Lean4Badge on assistant messages, pass handlers that post verifyLean4/retryLean4. Only show badge if lean4Available flag is true (sent from extension host on requestState based on lean4Service.isAvailable() && setting enabled).
